&lt;p&gt;We are currently advertising for experienced Health Visitors to work via our Trust Staff Bank supporting services and families throughout Kent working flexible hours . We share a common set of values and aspirations that reflect our values of being compassionate, aspirational, responsive and striving for excellence.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Health Visitors joining the Bank will be required to be proactive in delivering the Healthy Child Programme and be committed to delivering high quality care supporting our existing teams.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Health Visiting in Kent Community Health offers exciting opportunities to work with skill mix teams in corporate case-loads. If you are an experienced registered Specialist Community Public Health Nurse (a qualified Health Visitor) and would like to join the Bank to work flexible hours with our existing Health Visiting team , we would encourage you to apply to join our Staff Bank.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interview date is to be confirmed.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For more information about this role please contact&lt;/p&gt;
